More than 3000 citizens with mental disorders of the Chelyabinsk Oblast receive social services in a residential form in psycho-neurological boarding house (PNBH). The challenges that the system faces are: 
- The high cost of this form of service for the region;
- There are practically no alternatives to the residential form; 
- Limited opportunities for self-realization and employment of citizens with mental disorders;
- High risk of getting citizens with mental disorders living with elderly parents into PNBH.
